            <p class="pHome">When adding a new tool to this site to share with others there are a few 
                things to keep in mind.  See suggestions below.</p>
        </div></br>

        <p><b>Tool Name: Hammer.</b> <br/> 
            Try to be generic in the description so that a listing of 
            similar tools can be found when a fellow site user is viewing. The required image for each
             tool and where to buy link should be able to complete the picture with respect to what type of Hammer
             it may be.
            </p>

        <p><b>Tool Picture:</b> <br/> 
             This  should be a URL link to a clear image of the tool.</p>

        <p><b>Where To Purchase:</b> <br/> 
            This should be a URL link to the location of where this tools can 
            be puchased.  This link will also provode more detailed information on the tool if an 
            individual wants to do more detailed research on a specific tool.</p>

        <p><b>Recommended:</b> <br/> 
            Would recommend this tool based on your experience with it.  *** This information 
            will be expanded later for others to weigh in on existing tools on the site using 
            such as - likes - for a tool ***.</p>


